liveBlogPostPrepared.plaintext: Todd Murphy bowls Joe Root with a beauty! Great ball, turning so sharply out of the rough! Through the gate, a tremendous ball that kept a bit low - the second time in the series ROot has been done by a submariner! It's a great reward for Murphy, who denies Root a century. He's out for 91.
liveBlogPostPrepared.title: BOWLED HIM!

children.content: Todd Murphy bowls Joe Root with a beauty!
Great ball, turning so sharply out of the rough!
Through the gate, a tremendous ball that kept a bit low - the second time in the series ROot has been done by a submariner!
It's a great reward for Murphy, who denies Root a century.

liveBlogPostPrepared.plaintext: His 26th in Tests. 52 off 60 balls, seven fours, he's looked really quite good in the middle at The Oval today.
liveBlogPostPrepared.title: Bairstow has fifty!

children.content: 52 off 60 balls, seven fours, he's looked really quite good in the middle at The Oval today.

liveBlogPostPrepared.plaintext: Another session for England. The loss of Zak Crawley just after lunch and the chances Australia created around that suggested maybe they could get on top, but even the loss of Ben Stokes and Harry Brook in the latter half of the session hasn't slowed England down. Joe Root is 61 off 58 and he looks the second most comfortable of the partnership with Jonny Bairstow, whose 34 runs have come at almost a run a ball. England's lead is now 253, which already feels like ti could be beyond Australia, but there are still six wickets, including Root, Bairstow, Moeen Ali and Chris Woakes to come. If Australia can keep the target under 300 it will be a miracle.
liveBlogPostPrepared.title: TEA: England 4-265 (Root 61, Bairstow 34)
